    "Loop hunt round 2: upgrade-scroll targeting + flatline detection + taxidermist softlock (build 317). (1) Scroll-of-Upgrade slot mismatch: process_upgrade_scroll_action and process_identify_scroll_action iterated `inventory.items` in raw insertion order while the rest of the game uses get_sorted_inventory. Smart-policy aimed for the equipped weapon's sorted slot, so the upgrade landed on whichever junk pickup entered the bag first. Playtester scanned s=1 dwarf consuming 9 scrolls with the equipped Halberd still at +0 upg. Both scroll handlers now iterate the sorted view. (2) Equipped-weapon targeting in smart_policy.upgrade_scroll_mode: '1' fallback replaced with explicit lookup of the equipped weapon's position in the gear-only sorted view (weapon preferred over armor when both equipped). Hit-rate jumped from ~25% to 57% across the 159-seed grid. (3) Active-scroll-tier awareness: added active_scroll_item to obs + scroll_name on inventory entries so the inventory-mode reader skips upgrade scrolls when the equipped weapon is already at the scroll's tier cap (Basic +3, Greater +6, ... Eternal +35) AND skips when no weapon is equipped. Caught s=941 elf F9 at 504 idle turns spinning u<scroll>->1->c after the Halberd broke. The wedge Hail Mary path got the same gate. (4) Tighter flatline classifier: window narrowed from max(100, turns//4) to max(80, turns//5); HP-stability eased from max-min<=1 to <=3; new-tile-reached added to the progress signal set so an exploring fog-walker doesn't get flagged stuck. (5) Taxidermist softlock: process_taxidermist_action only accepts digit / 's' / 'i' / 'x' but the action hint claimed n/s/e/w worked too; policy returned _step_away() (a direction) when no trophies in bag, which the handler ignored, taxidermist_mode persisted forever. Caught s=941 elf F9 at 500 idle turns mashing 'w'. Hint corrected, policy returns 'x'. 159-seed × 3-race wide hunt: 0 stuck after fixes.",
    "Loop hunt round 1: three softlock fixes surfaced by status=stuck (build 316). (1) Variable-shadowing in playtest_report.to_html: the items-table aggregation loop reused the name 'status' for per-item bag-state, clobbering the outer alive/dead/stuck classifier value before the death_block branch and dropping the stuck-banner from the per-run page. Renamed to item_status (line 1161). (2) Blacksmith afford-gate: smart_policy returned '1'/'2' on worn gear without checking gold; the handler logs 'Not enough gold' but stays in blacksmith_mode, infinite loop. Added _repair_cost_est helper (80% of get_repair_cost) to the equipped slot dict and gated the repair returns on gold >= cost. Caught on s=1234 dwarf F5 (850+ turns mashing '2' with 4g). (3) Shrunk-stairs gate: Zot's shrinking spell on bug-levels blocks descent + ascent ('drop is lethal', 'stairs impossibly tall'); the handler stays in stairs_down_mode / stairs_up_mode and the policy mashed 'd' or 'u' forever. Added is_shrunk early-return that walks off the stair tile, plus a tier filter in game_loop wayfinder that strips D + U from priority tiers while shrunk so the agent doesn't immediately route back. Caught on s=461 elf F8 (176+ idle turns at HP 78/78). 159-seed × 3-race wide-hunt now shows 0 stuck (was 2 prior).",
